<p>As an example for the calculation of the MC for 3 cooks or 120th sandwich:
$$MC&#95;3 = \Delta TC&#95;3 / \Delta Q&#95;3 = (TC&#95;3 - TC&#95;2) / (Q&#95;3 - Q&#95;2) = (340 - 260) / (120 - 90)= 80/30 \approx $2.67$$</p>
<p>Because in this example the Labor Cost per Work is $80 the $$\Delta TC$$ is going to be always $80. Note that $$\Delta Q$$ is actually the Marginal Product of Labor that was added by the new worker.</p>
<p>The Marginal Cost answers the question: <em>How much does it cost to increase production of one sandwich?</em></p>

